profile_positions.description:
Urban Living Lab developer at AMS Institute. She is responsible for AMS coordination the Marineterrein Living Lab (MALL), the EU ATELIER project and other Living Labs activities. She is also involved in the Open Knowledge Coalition supporting the establishment of tangible collaborations between the member organizations: CODAM, AHK, AMS.

/Contribution 
//Living Lab coordination Marineterrein (MALL): In MALL she guides the experimenters in the onboarding, scoping, implementation and validation process of their solutions to be ready for upscaling and/or replication at urban scale.
//EU ATELIER: leads AMS contribution in the monitoring and evaluation of the implementation of the Innovation Ateliers in Amsterdam and Bilbao and in supporting the stakeholder engagement activities to accelerate energy transition in cities.
//Living Labs: develops and validates Living Labs (LL) tools and mature AMS LL way of working. She also contributes to the MADE LL course.

Andorra Living Lab
The Andorra Living Lab initiative combines different research topics (Tourism, Innovation, Energy & Environment, Mobility, Dynamic urban planning, and Education) for the future urban challenges of the country.
In this context, I have been conducting research that combines architecture and urban design, technology and computer science, and coordinated multiple activities in innovation projects with interdisciplinary teams, and multiple partners and stakeholders, from Public Institutions to Industry.


//TerMITes for Electronautes:
Engaging elementary school students in an educational experience that relates quantitative environmental measurements with their qualitative perceptions and feelings about the surrounding environment.


//Data Mining for Young Minds
Introducing Andorran (8-10 years old) kids to data mining. Through a series of workshops they discovered the process of extracting knowledge from data through an emotional city mapping.

//Andorra Innovation Space
Providing an open collaborative interdisciplinary space for researchers, companies, startups, and educational institutions that can bring people together and empower them to actively contribute to innovation and the entrepreneurial life of Andorra.

//Andorra Cultural Heritage
Introducing a new way to emphasize cultural heritage for tourists and citizens, and to put the culture at the foundation of the transformation and innovation process.

//CityScope Andorra
CityScope is a dynamic urban planning support system that includes an interactive LEGO model of the city for rapid-prototyping design options, real-time simulations, and visualizations.

//Other Projects

° City Science Lab Aalto /Map that Matters Workshop: Workshop organizer and Instructor. 
° TowerScope: Introduced a new concept for interactive building simulation.
° City Home: Design of multiple dynamic home configurations.
